ikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/MY24_Specialized_STATUS-2_140_REAR-SUS-DETAIL-SHOCK-ASSET_7454_MedRes-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/MY24_Specialized_STATUS-2_140_REAR-SUS-DETAIL-SHOCK-ASSET_7454_MedRes-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/MY24_Specialized_STATUS-2_140_REAR-SUS-DETAIL-SHOCK-ASSET_7454_MedRes-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/MY24_Specialized_STATUS-2_140_REAR-SUS-DETAIL-SHOCK-ASSET_7454_MedRes-2048x1365.jpg 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/MY24_Specialized_STATUS-2_140_REAR-SUS-DETAIL-SHOCK-ASSET_7454_MedRes-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/MY24_Specialized_STATUS-2_140_REAR-SUS-DETAIL-SHOCK-ASSET_7454_MedRes-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/MY24_Specialized_STATUS-2_DH_MID-3QUATERS_2126_MedRes-scaled.jpg\"><img width=\"1536\" height=\"1024\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/MY24_Specialized_STATUS-2_DH_MID-3QUATERS_2126_MedRes-1536x1024.jpg\" alt=\"Specialized Status 2\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/MY24_Specialized_STATUS-2_DH_MID-3QUATERS_2126_MedRes-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/MY24_Specialized_STATUS-2_DH_MID-3QUATERS_2126_MedRes-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/MY24_Specialized_STATUS-2_DH_MID-3QUATERS_2126_MedRes-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/MY24_Specialized_STATUS-2_DH_MID-3QUATERS_2126_MedRes-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/MY24_Specialized_STATUS-2_DH_MID-3QUATERS_2126_MedRes-2048x1365.jpg 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/MY24_Specialized_STATUS-2_DH_MID-3QUATERS_2126_MedRes-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/MY24_Specialized_STATUS-2_DH_MID-3QUATERS_2126_MedRes-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/MY24_Specialized_STATUS-2_140_MID-3QUATERS-FRAME-ASSET_2107_MedRes-scaled.jpg\"><img width=\"1536\" height=\"1024\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/MY24_Specialized_STATUS-2_140_MID-3QUATERS-FRAME-ASSET_2107_MedRes-1536x1024.jpg\" alt=\"Specialized Status 2\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/MY24_Specialized_STATUS-2_140_MID-3QUATERS-FRAME-ASSET_2107_MedRes-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/MY24_Specialized_STATUS-2_140_MID-3QUATERS-FRAME-ASSET_2107_MedRes-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/MY24_Specialized_STATUS-2_140_MID-3QUATERS-FRAME-ASSET_2107_MedRes-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/MY24_Specialized_STATUS-2_140_MID-3QUATERS-FRAME-ASSET_2107_MedRes-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/MY24_Specialized_STATUS-2_140_MID-3QUATERS-FRAME-ASSET_2107_MedRes-2048x1365.jpg 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/MY24_Specialized_STATUS-2_140_MID-3QUATERS-FRAME-ASSET_2107_MedRes-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/MY24_Specialized_STATUS-2_140_MID-3QUATERS-FRAME-ASSET_2107_MedRes-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/MY24_Specialized_STATUS-2_DH_PROFILE_0014_MedRes-scaled.jpg\"><img width=\"1536\" height=\"1025\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/MY24_Specialized_STATUS-2_DH_PROFILE_0014_MedRes-1536x1025.jpg\" alt=\"Specialized Status 2\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/MY24_Specialized_STATUS-2_DH_PROFILE_0014_MedRes-1536x1025.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/MY24_Specialized_STATUS-2_DH_PROFILE_0014_MedRes-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/MY24_Specialized_STATUS-2_DH_PROFILE_0014_MedRes-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/MY24_Specialized_STATUS-2_DH_PROFILE_0014_MedRes-768x513.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/MY24_Specialized_STATUS-2_DH_PROFILE_0014_MedRes-2048x1367.jpg 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/MY24_Specialized_STATUS-2_DH_PROFILE_0014_MedRes-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/MY24_Specialized_STATUS-2_DH_PROFILE_0014_MedRes-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>All three models rely on a redesigned M5 aluminum chassis that is engineered to be as durable as possible. Frame specifics include a Horst link suspension system with a geo pivot chip in the Horst pivot, a threaded bottom bracket, internal cable routing with external rear brake cable routing option, 12 x 148mm dropouts, SRAM UDH, and sealed bearing pivots. All Status 2s include mixed wheel sizes, but all frame sizes are not the same…</p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/MY24_Specialized_STATUS-2_S0_PROFILE_0021_MedRes-scaled.jpg\"><img width=\"1536\" height=\"1025\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/MY24_Specialized_STATUS-2_S0_PROFILE_0021_MedRes-1536x1025.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/MY24_Specialized_STATUS-2_S0_PROFILE_0021_MedRes-1536x1025.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/MY24_Specialized_STATUS-2_S0_PROFILE_0021_MedRes-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/MY24_Specialized_STATUS-2_S0_PROFILE_0021_MedRes-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/MY24_Specialized_STATUS-2_S0_PROFILE_0021_MedRes-768x513.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/MY24_Specialized_STATUS-2_S0_PROFILE_0021_MedRes-2048x1367.jpg 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/MY24_Specialized_STATUS-2_S0_PROFILE_0021_MedRes-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/MY24_Specialized_STATUS-2_S0_PROFILE_0021_MedRes-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>That’s because there is a new S0 size for both the 140 and 170 models. The S0 is a bike designed for riders under 5′, which comes with changes to provide the same rider experience for smaller, lighter riders. Instead of a 29/27.5″ mixed wheel setup, the S0 uses a 27.5/26″ MX setup, and includes custom-tuned kinematics with lower spring pressures and more progression. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>On the 170 S0, the frame also employs an air shock instead of a coil shock, along with narrower handlebars and shorter cranks. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>The Status 2 170 DH does not have an S0 size, so it will be offered in S2-S5 sizing. All sizes feature a 77º seat tube angle, or 77.6º in the high position, and a 63.5 or 64º head tube angle which can be made 0.5º steeper in the high position. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Specialized-Status-2-models.png\"><img width=\"1536\" height=\"450\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Specialized-Status-2-models-1536x450.png\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Specialized-Status-2-models-1536x450.png 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Specialized-Status-2-models-297x87.png 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Specialized-Status-2-models-120x35.png 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Specialized-Status-2-models-768x225.png 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Specialized-Status-2-models.png 1707w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Specialized-Status-2-models-specs.png\"><img width=\"954\" height=\"716\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Specialized-Status-2-models-specs.png\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Specialized-Status-2-models-specs.png 954w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Specialized-Status-2-models-specs-297x223.png 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Specialized-Status-2-models-specs-120x90.png 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Specialized-Status-2-models-specs-768x576.png 768w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>If you consider the S0 models as separate bikes, there are five different configurations of the new Status S2. Pricing starts at $2000 for the Status 2 170 frameset, and complete bikes start at $3,000 for the Status 170 S0 &amp; 140 S0. The Status 2 140 and 170 then sell for $3,500, and the Status 2 DH bumps up to $4,500. </p>\n\n\n\n<p><em><a href=\"https://www.specialized.com/us/en\">specialized.com</a></em></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/specialized-status-2-140mm-trail-bike-170mm-dh/\">Specialized Status 2 Expands with 140mm Trail Bike, Two 170mm Options</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Zach Overholt","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"ba0b91e5a47f24d3d0efd10107ab22bb4d5e608f8d315fddfe6ece221f5f68cf","category":"Cycling"}